  "prompt": "What are stars made out of?",
  "response": "Stars are primarily made out of hydrogen and helium, the two lightest and most abundant elements in the universe. In their cores, stars undergo nuclear fusion, a process where hydrogen atoms combine to form helium, releasing a tremendous amount of energy. This energy powers the star and causes it to shine. \n\nAs stars evolve, they can also produce heavier elements such as carbon, oxygen, and iron through fusion processes. The specific composition of a star can vary depending on its stage in the stellar lifecycle and its initial mass, but hydrogen and helium remain the primary constituents.",
